---
[v1] arm64: dts: mediatek: add qdma-pkt-rx-wdone support

Add the "mediatek,qdma-pkt-rx-wdone" property to the MT7988D RFB
device tree. Without this property, the QDMA may encounter a data
coherence issue on the MT7988D.
---
v1: Add "mediatek,qdma-pkt-rx-wdone" to mt7988d-rfb.dts.
---

From d7fff62ce71e93ae0345fe4f4a027c0e06001785 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: "chak-kei.lam" <chak-kei.lam@mediatek.com>
Date: Tue, 19 May 2026 14:41:38 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] arm64: dts: mediatek: add qdma-pkt-rx-wdone support

Without this patch, the QDMA may encounter a data coherence issue on the MT7988D.
---
 arch/arm64/boot/dts/mediatek/mt7988d-rfb.dts | 4 ++++
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+)

diff --git a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/mediatek/mt7988d-rfb.dts b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/mediatek/mt7988d-rfb.dts
index db751e2..b6c18a8 100644
--- a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/mediatek/mt7988d-rfb.dts
+++ b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/mediatek/mt7988d-rfb.dts
@@ -64,6 +64,10 @@
  * -ssusb1: usb@11200000 (u2 port and u3 port)
  */

+&eth {
+	mediatek,qdma-pkt-rx-wdone;
+};
+
 &pcie1 {
 	status = "disabled";
 };
-- 
2.45.2

